Datasets:

- SPY.csv, QQQ.csv, VTI.csv
    - the raw data for the etfs
    - Source: Yahoo Finance
    - Columns:
        - Date
            - The trading day
            - Type: Date
        - Open
            - The opening price of the etf
            - Type: Float
        - Close
            - The closing price of the etf
            - Type: Float
        - High
            - The highest price of the etf during that day
            - Type: Float
        - Low
            - The lowest price of the etf during that day
            - Type: Float
        - Adj Close
            - The adjusted closing price of the etf
            - Type: Float
        - Volume
            - Total number of shares sold that day
            - Type: Integer

- combined_prices.csv
    - combined data from SPY.csv, QQQ.csv, and VTI.csv using only the Adj Close and Date columns
    - Source: merging SPY.csv, QQQ.csv, VTI.csv
    - Columns:
        - Date
            - The trading day
            - Type: Date
        - SPY_Price
            - The adjusted closing price of SPY
            - Type: Float
        - QQQ_Price
            - The adjusted closing price of QQQ
            - Type: Float
        - VTI_Price
            - The adjusted closing price of VTI
            - Type: Float

- prices_and_indicators.csv
    - the prices of the etfs along with their moving averages calculated
    - Source: combine_prices.csv with added moving 50 day average column
    - Columns:
        - Date
            - The trading day
            - Type: Date
        - SPY_Price
            - The adjusted closing price of SPY
            - Type: Float
        - QQQ_Price
            - The adjusted closing price of QQQ
            - Type: Float
        - VTI_Price
            - The adjusted closing price of VTI
            - Type: Float
        - SPY_MA50
            - The 50-day moving average of SPY
            - Calculation:
                - Take the average of SPY_Price over the past 50 days
                - df["SPY_Price"].rolling(50).mean()
            - Type: Float
        - QQQ_MA50
            - The 50-day moving average of QQQ
            - Calculation:
                - Take the average of QQQ_Price over the past 50 days
                - df["QQQ_Price"].rolling(50).mean()
            - Type: Float
        - VTI_MA50
            - The 50-day moving average of SPY
            - Calculation:
                - Take the average of VTI_Price over the past 50 days
                - df["VTI_Price"].rolling(50).mean()
            - Type: Float

- single_buy_hold.csv, single_timing.csv, equal_buy_hold.csv, equal_timing.csv, custom_buy_hold.csv, custom_timing.csv
    - The simulations for each portfolio case
        - single_buy_hold.csv: Single ETF with Buy & Hold Strategy, using only SPY
        - single_timing.csv: Single ETF with Timing Strategy, using only SPY
        - equal_buy_hold.csv: Equal Investing Distribution with Buy & Hold Strategy, all ETFs are equally bought
        - equal_timing.csv: Equal Investing Distribution with Timing Strategy, all ETFs are equally bought and sold
        - custom_buy_hold.csv: Custom Investing Distribution with Buy & Hold Strategy, 50% go into SPY, 30% go into QQQ, 20% go into VTI
        - custom_timing.csv: Custom Investing Distribution with Timing Strategy, 50% go into SPY, 30% go into QQQ, 20% go into VTI
        - Assume Initial Investment is $10000, and biweekly contribution is $500

    - Source: prices_with_indicators.csv and adding columns to help with simulations
    - Columns:
        Columns:
        - Date
            - The trading day
            - Type: Date

        - SPY_Price
            - The adjusted closing price of SPY
            - Type: Float
        - QQQ_Price
            - The adjusted closing price of QQQ
            - Type: Float

        - VTI_Price
            - The adjusted closing price of VTI
            - Type: Float

        - SPY_MA50
            - The 50-day moving average of SPY
            - Calculation: already calculated from prices_with_indicators.csv
            - Type: Float

        - QQQ_MA50
            - The 50-day moving average of QQQ
            - Calculation: already calculated from prices_with_indicators.csv
            - Type: Float

        - VTI_MA50
            - The 50-day moving average of SPY
            - Calculation: already calculated from prices_with_indicators.csv
            - Type: Float

        - Position_SPY
            - indicates when to buy or sell shares, 1 being buy and 0 being sell
            - Calculation:
                - in all Buy & Hold simulutions, Position_SPY is always 1
                - in all Timing simulations
                    - 1 if SPY_Price > SPY_MA50
                    - else it is 0

                - if price > ma:
                    position = 1
                  else:
                    position = 0

            - Type: Integer/Boolean

        - Position_QQQ
            - indicates when to buy or sell shares, 1 being buy and 0 being sell
            - Calculation:
                - in all Buy & Hold simulutions, Position_QQQ is always 1
                - in all Timing simulations
                    - 1 if QQQ_Price > QQQ_MA50
                    - else it is 0

                - if price > ma:
                    position = 1
                  else:
                    position = 0

            - Type: Integer/Boolean

        - Position_VTI
            - indicates when to buy or sell shares, 1 being buy and 0 being sell
            - Calculation:
                - in all Buy & Hold simulutions, Position_VTI is always 1
                - in all Timing simulations
                    - 1 if VTI_Price > VTI_MA50
                    - else it is 0

                - if price > ma:
                    position = 1
                  else:
                    position = 0

            - Type: Integer/Boolean

        - Contribution
            - the amount contributed that day, contributions happen biweekly (or every 10 days)
            - Calculation:
                - Every 10 days, add the contribution amount (which is $500)
                - if i % 10 == 0:
                    contribution = 500

            - Type: Float

        - Cash
            - the available cash that can be used to buy shares (from biweekly contributions and profits from selling shares)
            - Calculation:
                - On the first row/initial investment
                    - Cash would be set to the Initial Investment amount ($10000)
                    - Cash will be used to buy the initial shares, so Cash will be back to 0
                    - Cash = 0 (After first shares calculations)

                - When contributions happen (when contribution is not 0)
                    - Add contribution amount to cash
                    - Cash + Contribution

                - When buying shares (When position is 1)
                    - take away from cash depending on the ETF's portfolio distribution amount
                    - Cash - Amount Invested
                        - Amount Invested = Cash * ETF Distribution
                        - Example:
                            - SPY in Custom Portfolio (SPY is 50%)
                            - Cash - (Cash * 0.5)

                    - amount = cash * weight
                      shares[etf] += amount / price
                      cash -= amount

                - When selling shares (when position is 0)
                    - add to cash depending on the number of shares the ETF has and the current price
                    - Cash + (Number of shares * ETF Price)

                    - cash += shares[etf] * price
                      shares[etf] = 0

                - *the Cash columns final amount is calculated after share calculations

            - Type: Float

        - Shares_SPY
            - shows how many shares of SPY the portfolio has during that day
            - Calculation:
                - For the initial investment or first date on the table
                    - Initial Investment / SPY_Price
                - For when Position_SPY is 1
                    - Use cash, the distribution amount for SPY, and SPY_Price to calculate amount
                    - (Cash * SPY Distribution Percent) / SPY_Price

                    - amount = cash * weight
                      shares[etf] += amount / price

                - For when Position_SPY is 0
                    - Add to cash using the distribution amount for SPY and SPY_Price to calculate amount
                    - Shares set to 0

            - Type: Float
        
        - Shares_QQQ
            - shows how many shares of QQQ the portfolio has during that day
            - Calculation:
                - In the single ETF portfolio, shares will always be 0
                - For the initial investment or first date on the table
                    - Initial Investment / QQQ_Price

                - For when Position_QQQ is 1
                    - Use cash, the distribution amount for QQQ, and QQQ_Price to calculate amount
                    - (Cash * QQQ Distribution Percent) / QQQ_Price

                    - amount = cash * weight
                      shares[etf] += amount / price

                - For when Position_QQQ is 0
                    - Add to cash using the distribution amount for QQQ and QQQ_Price to calculate amount
                    - Shares set to 0

            - Type: Float

        - Shares_VTI
            - shows how many shares of VTI the portfolio has during that day
            - Calculation:
                - In the single ETF portfolio, shares will always be 0
                - For the initial investment or first date on the table
                    - Initial Investment / VTI_Price

                - For when Position_VTI is 1
                    - Use cash, the distribution amount for VTI, and VTI_Price to calculate amount
                    - (Cash * VTI Distribution Percent) / VTI_Price

                    - amount = cash * weight
                      shares[etf] += amount / price

                - For when Position_VTI is 0
                    - Add to cash using the distribution amount for VTI and VTI_Price to calculate amount
                    - Shares set to 0

            - Type: Float

        - Total_Invested
            - the amount invested to date
            - Calculation:
                - The Initial Invesetment ($10000) plus the sum of all contributions to date
                - Initial Investment + sum(all contributions)
                
                - total_invested = 10000 (the first date)
                  total_invested += contribution (after the first date)
            
            - Type: Float

        - Porfolio_Value
            - The total value of the portfolio
            - Calculation:
                - The ETF prices * the number of shares for each, and cash
                - value = (
                    shares_spy * spy_price +
                    shares_qqq * qqq_price +
                    shares_vti * vti_price +
                    cash
                  )
            - Type: Float

        - Earnings
            - profits loss or gained based on total invested
            - Calculation:
                - Portfolio_Value − Total_Invested
                - df["Earnings"] = df["Portfolio_Value"] - df["Total_Invested"]
            - Type: Float

        - Daily_Return
            - the percentage change in portfolio value compared to the day before
            - Calculation:
                - (Value_today − Value_yesterday) / Value_yesterday
                - df["Daily_Return"] = df["Portfolio_Value"].pct_change()
            - Type: Percent

        - Strategy
            - the strategy used in the simulation
            - Calculation:
                - Either "Buy & Hold" or "Timing"
            - Type: String
        
        - Portfolio_Type
            - the portfolio case used in the simulation
            - Calculation:
                - "Single": 100% SPY
                - "Equal": 33.3% in SPY, QQQ, and VTI
                - "Custom": 50% in SPY, 30% in QQQ, and 20% in VTI
            - Type: String